Samba Financial Group (SAMBA) ,  Saudi
Arabia â€™s second-largest lender by market value, reduced the
money it had set aside to cover bad loans by 80 percent in the
second quarter.  Provisions declined to 11 million riyals ($4.1 million) in
the three months ended June 30, from 57.4 million riyals a year
